{title: Give Me The Roses While I Live}
{artist: Jimmy Martin}
{composer: Written by R.H. Cornelius and James Rowe}

[G]Wonderful things of folks are said
[D7]When they have passed [G]away

Roses adorn the narrow bed
[D7]Over the sleeping [G]clay
[C]Give me the roses [G]while I live
Trying to cheer me [D7]on
[G]Useless are flowers that you give
[D7]After the soul is [G]gone
Praises are heard not by the dead
[D7]Roses they cannot [G]speak
Let us not wait till souls have fled
[D7]Generous friends to [G]be
Repeat #2
Faults are forgiven when folks lie
[D7]Cold in a narrow [G]bed
Let us forgive them ere they die
[D7]Now should the words be [G]said
Repeat #2